Sentencas: In this work the evaluation of the usage of LSCF-SCFN composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell is presented.
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode

Sentencas: For the cathode preparation, typically used perovskite oxide La0.8Sr0.2Co0.2Fe0.8
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode

Sentencas: O3-delta was mixed with different quantities of highly catalytic SrCo0.2Fe0.6Ni0.2O3-delta material.
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode

Sentencas: The obtained cathode pastes were used in the construction of identical, electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC cells, consisting of the composite cathode, Ce0.85Gd0.15O1.925 electrolyte and 8YSZ-Ni cermet anode.
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode

Sentencas: Open circuit voltage (OCV), current density-voltage and cell power density characteristics were measured in the 600-800 degrees C temperature range.
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode

Sentencas: Additionally, the analysis of recorded impedance spectra allowed us to determine the temperature dependence of ohmic resistance, charge transfer resistance and diffusion resistance of the cells.
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode

Sentencas: Comparing to the cell with unmodified cathode, substantial increase (60%-70%) of the maximum power density was observed for the cell with cathode modified by an addition of 20 wt.% of SrCo0.2Fe0.6Ni0.2O3-delta.
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode

Sentencas: Such an increase occurred despite that the impedance spectroscopy measurements suggest that the ohmic resistance of the electrolyte is a power limiting factor of the constructed cells.
Titulo: Electrolyte-supported IT-SOFC with LSCF-SCFN composite cathode
